prediction:
Correct answer: 2. Right umbilical artery

The ligament incised during the surgery is the falciform ligament of the liver. The falciform ligament is a fibrous structure that attaches the liver to the anterior abdominal wall. It is formed by the fusion of the umbilical vein and the ductus venosus. The ductus venosus is a remnant of the embryonic ductus venosus that connects the left and right umbilical veins. The right umbilical artery is also a remnant of the embryonic blood vessels.
